    <control translate="no">touch</control>
  </supports>

  <description>
    <p>Keycord works with folders that use the standard pass layout. Existing stores stay on disk as normal pass stores, so you can keep using compatible tools.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Open one or more password stores and search by name, store, field, regular expression, or structured find query</li>
      <li>Edit entries with form fields or raw pass-file text, generate passwords, and copy passwords, usernames, or one-time login codes</li>
      <li>Add existing stores, create new stores, import passwords on supported systems, or restore a store from Git with the Host backend</li>
      <li>Manage store recipients, folder-specific .gpg-id files, private keys, FIDO2 security keys, and OpenPGP smartcards</li>
      <li>Sync Git-backed stores, manage remotes, sign changes, and inspect history with commit verification details</li>
      <li>Use the adaptive GTK interface with keyboard, pointer, or touch on desktop and mobile Linux</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

